<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-128-378  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 128 378.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Feb 5 1990 n576 p18(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NTT devises erbium amp: Optical signals hiked 2,000 times. (NipponTelegraph and Telephone Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Lammers, David.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp announces that it has createdan erbium-doped optical fiber amplifier that can amplify opticalsignals by 2,000 times.andP;  The amplifier is small enough to be usedin optical transmission equipment, as a repeater in opticalsystems, for optical measurement instruments and for cabletelevision systems.andP;  The erbium amplifiers may eliminate the needto convert optical signals to electronic signals in order toamplify them.andP;  The amplifiers work by pumping light with energysupplied by a 0.98-micron wavelength semiconductor laser that hasstability of more than 3,500 hours at an output power of 30 mW.andO;The amplifier more than doubles the best-reported amplificationefficiency and triples the previous best emission efficiency with80 percent less power consumption.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Nippon Telegraph and Telephone Corp. (research).andO;Topic:     AmplifiersOptical CommunicationsTransmission LinesFiber OpticsResearch and Development.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>